### TaskFlow API — REST Client requests
### Open in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client) or
### Jetbrains' built-in HTTP Client. Run requests by clicking "Send Request"
### above each block.

@host = http://localhost:5000
@adminKey = change_me_only_used_for_first_admin

### --- 1. Health ---
GET {{host}}/api/health

### --- 2. Bootstrap an Admin (first run only) ---
POST {{host}}/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Demo Admin",
  "email": "admin@taskflow.dev",
  "password": "admin1234",
  "role": "Admin",
  "phone": "+910000000000",
  "adminKey": "{{adminKey}}"
}

### --- 3. Login (capture the token) ---
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@taskflow.dev",
  "password": "admin1234"
}

@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### --- 4. Who am I ---
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- 5. Create a department ---
# @name createDept
POST {{host}}/api/departments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Engineering",
  "description": "Software & infrastructure"
}

@deptId = {{createDept.response.body.department._id}}

### --- 6. Create an employee ---
# @name createEmp
POST {{host}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Asha Frontend",
  "email": "asha@taskflow.dev",
  "password": "asha1234",
  "role": "Employee",
  "department": "{{deptId}}"
}

@employeeId = {{createEmp.response.body.user._id}}

### --- 7. Create a task ---
# @name createTask
POST {{host}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Ship login page",
  "description": "Wire to /api/auth",
  "assignedToUser": "{{employeeId}}",
  "priority": "High",
  "deadline": "2026-05-15T17:00:00Z"
}

@taskId = {{createTask.response.body.task._id}}

### --- 8. List tasks ---
GET {{host}}/api/tasks?status=Pending&priority=High&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- 9. Get one task ---
GET {{host}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- 10. Update task status ---
PUT {{host}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "status": "In Progress" }

### --- 11. Add a comment ---
POST {{host}}/api/tasks/{{taskId}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "text": "Working on this now." }

### --- 12. Dashboard summary ---
GET {{host}}/api/dashboard/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- 13. Productivity report (last 30 days) ---
GET {{host}}/api/dashboard/productivity?days=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- 14. Notifications ---
GET {{host}}/api/notifications?unreadOnly=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- 15. WhatsApp parser dry-run (Admin only) ---
POST {{host}}/api/whatsapp/test/parse
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "message": "Assign task: Submit report by Friday to Asha priority high" }

### --- 16. Simulate a Twilio inbound webhook (works only when TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN is unset) ---
POST {{host}}/api/whatsapp/inbound
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

From=whatsapp:+910000000000&Body=Assign task: Daily standup at 10am to Asha
